13.plot: Sidekick-Man realizes that to Jammbo-Man he is nothing but a petty assistant. That will make Sidekick-Man reconsider his loyalties and adopt a new and terrible personality. He will become ... the archenemy! Will he defeat Jammbo-Man?

15.title: Princess Smile
15.plot: An accident with a toothbrush causes Princess to lose her smile. Rita will feel so sad that she'll promise not to brush her teeth ever again. Her friends will do their best to prevent this from happening and, incidentally, make princess recover her smile.

16.title: The Sticker
16.plot: The King finds some old stickers which are used to show that someone has a special talent. Bello will do his best to get a big sticker but unfortunately, things won't end up as he imagined. Or maybe they will.

18.title: The Plant
18.plot: The kids find it really fun to show their skills in gardening and to take care of a very special plant. Unfortunately, to take good care of something you need to be persevering, a very difficult thing for Bello.

19.title: Repetition Repetition
19.plot: Rita learns a new game, and she is very good at it. The repetition game. She will try the patience of all her friends over and over. There's only one option to make Rita understand how tiresome she can be, confront her with the best imitator in the galaxy.

20.title: The Perfect Toy
20.plot: Bello and Goomo get into a very challenging project... Designing the perfect toy! A toy that has everything a kid would want, so great that you could never get tired of it. After developing some ideas they'll find out that that object is a lot closer than they have ever imagined.

21.title: The Camping Trip
21.plot: The kids leave the neighbourhood for their first camping trip without the King and the Queen. Their lack of organization and laziness will turn everything into a mess. Only by working together and being creative will they be able to turn a critical situation into a fun camping experience.

22.title: Choose Me
22.plot: Being the last one to be picked for a team is always hard. But if you consider yourself as the best player and it's you own best friend who doesn't pick you, then it's even harder. This is what happens to Bello, and he is not going to take it very well.

23.title: My Turn
23.plot: The Queen shows the kids one of her favourite toys as a child: A trampoline! They all deduce to take turns to use it, but Rita doesn't want to come down and doesn't let anyone else play, so the others decide to force her to come down. But her endless energy will put her friends to the test.

24.title: Jammbo TV
24.plot: The group is having a lot of fun in the castle watching an exciting animation series. When the program ends, Goomo decides to stay a little more in front of the TV. And he ends up staying there for days! his friends will have to find a way to bring back the active and fun Goomo they all know.

1.title: The Instant Gardener
1.plot: In hopes of impressing the Queen with his gardening know-how, Bello uses a super grow formula that makes plants (and a dodo) grow wild and out of control! In taming the wild things Bello comes to understand how plants grow naturally on Jammbo and how things take their time.

2.title: Mamma Mina
2.plot: Mina is reluctantly drawn into a mission to help a lost dodo. Rita, with her self-professed "knowledge" of dodos, only makes matters worse. After a long search, thanks to Mina's failed experiment, the dodo's parents are lured to their lost babe. And though the dodo returns to its home, Mina has made a beloved little friend.

3.title: Mina's Party
3.plot: Mina wants to be the go to girl for fun on Jammbo. She tries to create Jammbo's best party ever. When her Four Phase Fun Plan fails to achieve "Maximum Fun-ness" for the group, Mina learns to chill and listen to her friends for ideas on how to get the good times flowing.

4.title: Promises, Promises
4.plot: Bello and Goomo promise to watch over Rita's favorite doll Princess while she goes off to the forest to play with Dodos, but they forget when they go off to play Jellyball. The unattended Princess is scooped up by King who wants to show his kingdom to the Royal visitor. The boys must lay siege to the castle to get Princess before Rita returns.

5.title: Super Jelly League
5.plot: Bello and Goomo, in their super-hero guises Jammboman and Sidekickman, create imaginary adventures which become moot when the super-hero wannabes are called into a real adventure - saving Rita, stranded on a ledge over Jammbo Gorge.

6.title: Best Friends Forever
6.plot: Goomo thinks Bello is his best friend. But, does Bello feel the same about him? Goomo sets out to test their friendship but the constant testing makes Bello run in the opposite direction. Upset with each other, they go off to play with "other friends", but they discover that nobody is more fun and understands your special nature like your BFF (Best Friend Forever).

7.title: I Want That Too
7.plot: The King is having a blast with his favorite Jelvis toy when Rita asks to play with it. King, who fancies himself a good sharer, lets her. Rita takes advantage and soon tricks him out of ALL his toys! Eventually she discovers the best thing about toys; when you share them with others you have a lot more fun.

8.title: Rita Adopts a Dodo
8.plot: Rita finally gets close enough to a dodo to pet it but only because it injured its foot. She takes the critter home, nursing it with affection and too much food. The now overweight dodo needs exercise badly. Rita learns that caring for others requires what is good for them, not for you. And, in doing so, now has a new best friend.

9.title: The Jelly Must Flow
9.plot: On a seemingly normal day, Goomo steps outside for a nice jog when he notices that something is slightly different about Jammbo today...everything has stopped moving! The music has stopped. The dodos are frozen mid-air. Even his friends are stiff as statues! It's up to Goomo and his helpful headphones to find out what happened and get Jammbo flowing again.

10.title: Flower Fear
10.plot: While exploring the musical nature of spring on Jammbo, Goomo realizes he has a fear of Burst into Song flowers. In search of a cure, Mina conducts a series of tests to help Goomo deal with his over the top reactions to the singing plants. In the end, Goomo realize that when you understand your fears, there is nothing scary at all.

11.title: Radio Goomo
11.plot: Goomo's discovers a noisy Heavy Metal Rock music box which he thinks is awesome but drives everyone elso on Jammbo crazy. Something must be done! Bello and Mina fool Goomo with a magic trick that makes the box "disappear". Without his "Wamma Jamma" box Goomo is distraught. Bello and Mina realize how important Goomo's music is to him and make the box reappear...

12.title: Royal Roommate
12.plot: Due to King's weird sleep habits, Queen kicks him out of the castle. Surrounded by dark shadows and unusual sounds, King quickly seeks refuge at Bello's house, but they are a long way from a good night's sleep. After a series of strange bedtime rituals, Bello's finally understands the problem and helps King conquer his fear of the night.

13.title: Tree Mystery
13.plot: Goomo falls asleep in the jellyberry grove. Nearby, King tries to open his soda bottle with a ridiculously powerful machine that ends up knocking over the jellyberry trees! Goomo wakes among the ruins horrified! He convinces himself that he is to blame! It's up to Bello and Mina to gather clues that get the King to take responsibility for his actions and clear Goomo's confused mind.

14.title: Inventor Bello
14.plot: Mina invents a giant robot for changing light bulbs on Jammbo. Bello thinks the robot should be made to defend Jammbo from invaders! Without Mina's knowledge, he modifies "Jammbobot" causing it to malfunction and rampage through the planet. Bello discovers the meaning behind the words "don't touch my stuff!".

15.title: Sound Detective
15.plot: The Queen's Song Fruit are being stolen from the royal garden. It's up to the detective duo of Jammboman and Sidekickman to solve this crime. Everyone is a suspect. Their listening skills and teamwork help them catch the fruit filcher. It's quite a surprise---even to the thief.

16.title: Rita Loses Princess
16.plot: During teatime, Rita loses track of Princess. She searches Jammbo in a frantic frenzy but fails to find her best friend. Bello sees Rita's upset. He vows to make her have so much fun, that she'll forget Princess. And he does! But, when Princess reappears, it's Bello who feels friendless.

17.title: Queen Rita
17.plot: The Queen goes on vacation, leaving King with lots of responsibilities. He leaps into action, finding someone else to do it. Rita will help the King...if she's made Queen of Jammbo! At first, all the kids are happy one of their own is in charge. But, soon the fun and games are replaced by games that make only Rita happy. The tiny Queen must realize how the power is going to her head.

18.title: Scary Story
18.plot: The kids are sitting around a campfire telling scary stories. Goomo tells the scariest monster story and then goes off to get a snack. But, he's gone too long! The others must look for him in the dark woods! Before long mysterious shadow and sounds have them all thinking a monster is stalking them!

21.plot: Bello is put in charge of the music factory, but he doesn't read the instruction manual and gets into a bit of a mess.

23.title: Operation Save Jammbo
23.plot: Jammbo's in trouble! Its amazing music bubbles are full of trash and gunky goo. After a planet wide investigation, the King, Queen and kids realize that the junk in the bubbles is their own garbage! They work together to change their sloppy habits and restore Jammbo's jelly-good health. In the process they recycle their garbage into something they can all enjoy.

24.title: Experiments in Invisibility
24.plot: Thanks to some breakthrough science, Mina is able to make objects, and herself, invisible! She can't help but see the effects of invisibility on her unsuspecting friends! After a day of wild happenings the kids discover the culprit of all the invisible weirdness. They come up with an experiment of their own to see how much the scientist likes being tested!

26.title: The Haunted Castle
26.plot: Spooked by lighting and thunder, Bello and Goomo seek refuge in the Music Factory. But once inside, they realize there's much scarier stuff afoot; there's a ghost in the castle that's frightening the dodos and keeping them from making music bubbles! And if the dodos stop, Jammbo has no music. If there's no music, the planet freezes! Yikes! It's up to the boys to find the ghost ...

27.title: Inner Space
27.plot: The King doesn't want to share his new rocket powered skateboard so he hides it in a magic box. Goomo and Bello decide to claim it, challenging the King's wishes, and end up in a new and larger world. A world of fun and....danger.

28.title: Queen's Birthday
28.plot: The Queen feels gloomy. The King and the children agree to organize the best birthday party ever. Unfortunately each of the participants has a very particular idea as to how to organize the Queen's surprise party. Its success will depend on their capacity to put themselves "in each others' shoes"...especially the Queen's.

29.title: My Little Queen
29.plot: Bello is fed up with the Queen, whom he thinks tries to ruin all his adventures and games. On a starry night, full of shooting stars, Bello makes a wish: may the Queen become a young girl again so she can let him do anything he wants. When Bello's wish comes true, he will have to act like the crazy little Queen's older brother and realizes the task can be hard, difficult and at times ...

30.title: Goomo's Birthday
30.plot: It's Goomo's birthday and his hopes are high. Unfortunately, he wakes to find his precious helmet missing! On top of that his friends are acting strangely and they all appear to have forgotten all about his birthday. Goomo would be happy to have things simply return to normal. Luckily, he's in for a surprise that could make this day a very special one indeed.

31.title: Jammbo's Many Worlds
31.plot: Ongo hurt himself while playing with Bello and Goomo so he must stay at home to rest for several days. Bello feels guilty and decides to move into Ongo's house until his friend feels better. Their different views on life will meet and together they'll discover that everything, even the smallest detail, can be enjoyed if seen with open eyes.

32.title: Great Student
32.plot: Rita tries her own experiments in Mina's lab. She'll soon discover she first needs to learn some basics in order to avoid a disaster.

33.title: Unexpected Pianist
33.plot: Bello discovers his best friend has an innate talent for music. From that moment on, he will try to share his discovery with the rest of his friends. Despite how shy Goomo is, Bello will try to reveal and share the secret.

34.title: Ultravision
34.plot: Goomo has lost the glasses he uses to play Jammboman and Helmetkid with Bello. Both friends discover a blind Dodo wearing Goomo's glasses. With them on, the Dodo can actually see and play with the rest of the Dodos. Will Goomo give up his glasses or take them back to be a superhero?

35.title: One Note Universe
35.plot: Rita and Princess are having a lovely pink picnic: pink dishes, pink food, pink everything! Rita confides in Princess how she would like everything on Jammbo to be her favorite color. She rushes to the Music Factory and switches the multi-colored music bubbles to pink which threatens to make everything look and sound the same!

36.title: Wild Nature
36.plot: Goomo and Rita enjoy their day in the outdoors when they suddenly discover a Dodo egg. The children and the small egg will go on an action-packed adventure. Will the egg survive after so much hustle and bustle?

37.title: Soundcatchers
37.plot: The Disk of Sounds has gone crazy and all the sounds in Jammbo have been changed, causing a huge chaos. Bello and Rita will be in charge of returning each sound to the place where it belongs.

38.title: One-Eyed Bello
38.plot: Bello has to wear an eye patch. He feels uncomfortable and discouraged because of how he looks. Luckily, his friends use the wisdom of a song to remind him that any problem can turn into something fun.

39.title: Goomo's Race
39.plot: Goomo has decided to take 100.000 steps with a pair of magic sneakers that will lead him to an amazing treasure. At least that's what he believes because his friends think he's gone crazy. In the end, who wins?

40.title: Agent Mina
40.plot: What does a special agent need? What amazing inventions can we create with our everyday objects? Mina has the answer. She'll soon prove to her friends that science doesn't need to be boring. In fact it can be a secret agents' best resource.

41.title: Colour of Fun
41.plot: The children get wound up in a tag-playing competition to see who the best team in the universe is. So, what's wrong with that? They begin to see the other team members as enemies even when they're not playing. Someone will have to teach them the difference between rivalry and turning against each other.

42.title: Flying Bathtub
42.plot: The King is impatient to try out his new acquisition: a bathtub that flies to music. When the King steps away momentarily, Bello and Mina end up being the first to try it.

43.title: Silent Sheriff
43.plot: Bello suddenly has great powers thanks to a sheriff star badge that grants his every wish. His new responsibility empowers him so much that Bello ends up wishing for something he'll soon regret.

44.title: Back-Up
44.plot: The King has hurt his back. Everyone thinks of a plan to transport him -safe and sound - to his comfortable bed back in the castle. They must learn to listen to each other and consider even the most absurd options because you never know where the answer might be.

47.title: White Dodo
47.plot: The children get a surprise visit from a White Dodo. All of them, especially Ongo, make friends with this incredible animal. Unfortunately, the White Dodo has a mission to accomplish and a separation seems inevitable. Despite the sad goodbye, there is always music to cheer them up.

48.title: Questions, Questions
48.plot: Mina is in awe after reading Yidoro The Wise's biography. For her, there is nothing more important than wisdom. That's why she will avoid asking questions that would reveal her ignorance. To her surprise there are things that everyone else knows, except her. Soon she will understand the importance of always asking questions to those who know.

49.title: Super Speed
49.plot: Bello and Goomo dream of becoming real super heroes so they ask Mina to train them. She sets out to do a great job but Bello isn't ready to endure the long and hard training. He gives up and choses an easier activity. Something he will later regret.

50.title: Look at Me!
50.plot: It's not always easy to stand still when everyone else gets praise and applause. Bello will try to steal the show during his friends' performances. They get so upset that Bello will need to share some of his talent to fix things.

51.title: Game Surprise
51.plot: Bello andy Goomo are faced with an almost impossible task when they discover that all the toys in the castle have been placed in a single box. The temptation is great but they have strict orders not to touch the box for they would surely make a huge mess. Will they be able to obey that order and keep the castle spotless?

52.title: Jammbo's Rhythm
52.plot: Is there a better place to dance than the planet where music is born? Every person on Jammbo has a dance to show you so we can all dance together to the rhythm of Jammbo.

imdb.plot outline: Join Bello and his Jelly Jamm friends as they share exciting adventures on their home planet of Jammbo, where music is born. Laugh and learn with these magical friends as they use fun and creativity to face their fears, solve everyday problems and learn to live together in happiness and harmony.
imdb.title: Jelly Jamm
